McCloney's career began in 1984 when he won a lip-sync contest at Minneapolis' First Avenue nightclub  impersonating Little Richard, Screamin' Jay Hawkins, and James Brown.
He began performing stand-up in 1989, performing locally and opening for Richard Pryor, Little Richard and Chris Rock.
Also in 1989, McCloney debuted a talk show, Get Down With It, on local cable-access Minneapolis Television Network.
